Australia, also known as the Commonwealth of Australia, is a sovereign country comprising the mainland of the Australian continent, the island of Tasmania, and numerous smaller islands. The capital city is Canberra and other major cities include Sydney, Melbourne, Brisbane, Perth and Adelaide.

The official language spoken in Australia is English but there are various indigenous languages from different groups such as Aboriginal people all around the country. Some common greetings used by Australians include "G'day" which means "Good Day," "How's it going?", or simply "Hello."

According to World Bank data from 2019 (prior to COVID-19), Australia has an excellent economy with a GDP growth rate at 1.8 percent annually thanks to its natural resources such as minerals including coal and iron ore that they export globally along with agricultural products.
